Package uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.gui

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CONTEXTPhlogenomicDatasetBrowser
    A runnable GUI main-class application for browsing phylogenomic datasets (phylogenies and multiple sequence alignments, both batch-loadable)
    DisplayAlignment  
    DisplayAlignmentPanel
    Class to extend JPanel to paint alignments directly as rendered java.awt.Graphics2D canvasses.
    DisplayPhylogeny
    A class to hold data and display information about phylogenies, which can be specified as either TreeNode or NewickTreeRepresentation
    DisplayPhylogenyFactory
    This is a factory object: the the factory methods are called in static context to create an array of DisplayPhylogeny objects from DisplayPhylogenyFactory#fromFile(), DisplayPhylogenyFactory#fromTreeNode(), DisplayPhylogenyFactory#fromNewickTreeRepresentation(), and DisplayPhylogenyFactory#fromString() inputs.
    DisplayPhylogenyPanel
    A JPanel that displays a cladogram-type representation of a phylogeny.
    GCPMinimalAlignmentCompareLocal
    TableRenderDemo is just like TableDemo, except that it explicitly initializes column sizes and it uses a combo box as an editor for the Sport column.
    GCPViewerApplet  
    GeneralConvergencePipelineApplication
    Launcher / entry-point and application for a genome convergence detection pipeline and graphical user interface (GUI)
    TableRenderDemoGCP
    TableRenderDemo is just like TableDemo, except that it explicitly initializes column sizes and it uses a combo box as an editor for the Sport column.
    TableRenderDemoGCPMinimal
    TableRenderDemo is just like TableDemo, except that it explicitly initializes column sizes and it uses a combo box as an editor for the Sport column.
